Title : Portal:Current events/2014 May 1
Text : <!-- All news items below this line -->{{Current events header|2014|05|01}}

;Armed conflicts and attacks
*[[2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine]]:
**Pro-Russian militants seize the regional prosecutor's office in the [[Eastern Ukraine|eastern Ukrainian]] city of [[Donetsk]].  [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-27243753 (BBC)]
**Ukraine announces that it is reintroducing [[conscription]]. [http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2617592/Preparing-war-Ukraine-puts-troops-combat-alert-Russian-invasion-weeks-inaction-against-pro-Kremlin-uprising.html (''Daily Mail'')]
*[[Islamist insurgency in Nigeria]]:
**A [[car bomb]] attack in the Nigerian capital [[Abuja]] kills at least nine people. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-27249097 (BBC)]

;Arts and cuture
*Egypt opens a 3D-printed full-sized exact [[replica]] of King [[Tutankhamun]]'s [[KV62]] tomb in the [[Valley of the Kings]], as officials announce that a 30-day [[Visa_(document)|visa]] purchased at the airport will be two thirds more expensive. [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/may/01/exact-replica-tutankhamun-tomb-egypt (The Guardian)] [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/travel/destinations/africaandindianocean/egypt/10801168/Egypt-visa-costs-rise-as-replica-Tutankhamun-tomb-opens.html (The Daily Telegraph)]

;Business and economy
*[[Ford]] announces that their current chief executive officer, [[Alan Mulally]], will be retiring in July, and that their chief operating officer [[Mark Fields (businessman)|Mark Fields]] will be taking his place.  [https://www.bbc.com/news/business-27238248 (BBC)]

;Disasters and accidents
*An explosion on a train in the [[Chennai Central railway station|central railway station]] in the Indian city of [[Chennai]] kills at least one person and injures ten. [http://www.ndtv.com/article/india/blast-at-chennai-railway-station-10-injured-516619 (NDTV)]

;Health and environment
*The first-ever [[2013–14 Chikungunya outbreak|outbreak]] of [[chikungunya]] in the Caribbean reaches epidemic levels. [https://web.archive.org/web/20140503071055/http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/latestnews/Chikungunya-now-an-epidemic-in-the-Caribbean (''Jamaica Observer'')]

;International relations
*The [[China|People's Republic of China]] and [[Russia]] announce plans to hold joint [[naval exercise]]s in the [[East China Sea]] in late May amid regional tensions about islands and airspace. [http://bigstory.ap.org/article/china-russia-hold-east-china-sea-naval-drills (AP)]

;Law and Crime
*[[Sinn Féin]] leader [[Gerry Adams]] remains in custody in connection with the [[Provisional Irish Republican Army|IRA]] [[murder of Jean McConville]]. [https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-27233712 (BBC)]

